cs.SI, cs.SOC, cs.IR, cs.CL, cs.CYBER. 

This paper investigates the behavior and content of extreme users on Twitter, which falls under the categories of social media analysis and social network analysis. Therefore, cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) and cs.SOC (Social and Sociological Aspects of Computing) are the most likely categories. The paper also analyzes the content of tweets, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses anomalous behavior and information sharing, which could fall under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
